1
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,036
<i>(</i># <i>"Eye of the Tiger" by Survivor)</i>

2
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:56,878
# <i>Risin' up</i>

3
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,956
# <i>Back on the street</i>

4
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:02,552
# <i>Did my time, took my chances</i>

5
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,637
# <i>Went the distance,</i>
<i>now I'm back on my feet</i>

6
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,913
# <i>Just a man and his will to survive</i>

7
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:15,430
# <i>So many times, it happens too fast</i>

8
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:18,958
# <i>You change your passion for glory</i>

9
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,949
# <i>Don't lose your grip</i>
<i>on the dreams of the past</i>

10
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:27,709
# <i>You must fight just to keep them alive</i>

11
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:31,992
# <i>It's the eye of the tiger,</i>
<i>it's the thrill of the fight</i>

12
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:36,318
# <i>Risin' up to the challenge of our rival</i>

13
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:40,479
# <i>And the last known survivor</i>
<i>stalks his prey in the night</i>

14
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:47,312
# <i>And he's watchin' us all</i>
<i>in the eye of the tiger</i>

15
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:53,350
- Come on! We made a deal.
- I know, but it's extremely crazy.

16
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:56,790
It's mentally irregular,
but it makes all the sense in the world.

17
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,514
- You owe me a favour.
- I know, but, uh...

18
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:02,791
- When did you think of this?
- About three years ago.

19
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:07,516
- This is very crazy, Apollo.
- Stallion, when you won that last fight...

20
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,074
...you won by one second.
You beat me by one second.

21
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:12,953
That's very hard for a man
of my intelligence to handle.

22
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,753
Didn't you say you learned
how to live with it?

23
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,836
- I lied.
- Oh, you lied?

24
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:21,077
Oh! So now you just gotta
prove it to yourself, right?

25
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:24,158
Just for myself. No TV,
no newspapers - just you and me.

26
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,794
Nothin' - just you and me.
Age before beauty.

27
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:30,310
- Anything you say.
- I do all the work. OK.

28
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:34,558
I tell you, Apollo, you'd better go slow.
You ain't as young as springtime no more.

29
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:38,719
- I'm still young enough to whip <i>your</i> butt.
- Oh, yeah? How you gonna do that?

30
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:42,196
- You taught me everything you know.
- <i>Almost</i> everything.

31
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:46,677
You gotta remember: You fight great,
but <i>I'm</i> a great fighter. You ready?

32
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,716
- Absolutely.
- You know, Stallion...

33
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:54,393
...it's too bad we gotta get old, huh?

34
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:57,035
Oh, just keep punchin', Apollo.

35
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:02,157
- Wanna ring the bell?
- All right.

36
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:04,669
Ding, ding.

37
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,236
Come on, Stallion.

38
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,911
Come on, come on.

39
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:13,316
Boy, you really move
good for an older guy.

40
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,396
- Look at him fly.
- Look out now.

41
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,676
No, you don't want any of this.

42
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:21,475
- <i>(Apollo)</i> Come on.
- Maybe I'm in here with the wrong guy.

43
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,798
Dad, you're late. Mom's gonna yell at you.

44
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,836
- So how you doin'?
- Fine.

45
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:50,679
You know, don't you think
that's a little bright?

46
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,394
- A little bit?
- Where'd you get that hat?

47
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:57,149
- A friend gave it to me. Like it?
- Who punched you in the eye?

48
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:01,748
- Same friend.
- That's weird. Better hurry, Dad.

49
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:04,952
You know, you're developin'
a very, very loud personality.

50
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:08,390
Don't go too fast,
or you're gonna get out of focus.

51
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:11,034
Oh, really? Wuh-ha-ha-ha!

52
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:17,596
- Yo!
- <i>(man)</i> Yo. It's about time.

53
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,472
I'm sorry I'm late.

54
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:23,070
- Why don't you go and get ready to eat?
- Great. You're here.

55
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:26,749
- Now you can stop calling him names.
- You been callin' me names?

56
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:29,348
We wait any longer,
it'll be my next birthday.

57
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:32,233
- Where have you been?
- Oh, uh, gettin' punched.

58
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:35,397
Bring the cake in and we can
get this celebration under way.

59
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:38,557
- Boy, am I hungry.
- Baby, why don't you get the cake?

60
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,194
We got a great surprise.
You're gonna love this cake.

61
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:43,550
- And your present.
- Where is it?

62
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:47,195
Let me set the mood. I gotta turn
the lights down and everythin'.

63
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:49,550
- Watch this.
- Is it parked outside?

64
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,240
Just be patient, would ya?

65
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:55,113
I'm so excited, I'm startin' to sweat.

66
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:59,870
I feel like I'm gettin' ready to go into
a big fight or somethin'. Watch this.

67
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,798
<i>(electronic voice) Happy birthday, Paulie.</i>

68
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,760
- What the hell is this?
- Your present.

69
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:27,316
I wanted a sports car for my birthday,
not no walkin' trash can!

70
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:30,398
- Come on! He looks great.
- This is extremely psycho.

71
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:32,909
You have no friends,
so we thought you'd like it.

72
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:35,838
Pretend you're happy.
It'll keep you company.

73
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,474
- That's a great-lookin' guy.
<i>- Please make a wish.</i>

74
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,397
It's creepy! It talks!

75
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:43,478
Creepy? I wish I had one of these
when I was growin' up.

76
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:47,115
- Go on, make a wish, like he says.
- I wish I wasn't in this nightmare.

77
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,754
Very classy wish. What do you think?

78
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:52,314
- <i>(bleeps)</i>
- Very good, huh?

79
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:54,670
You wanna help me
put out this forest fire?

80
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,997
- Sure.
- OK. On the count of three. One...

81
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,076
...two... three!

82
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,276
Whoa! Whoa!

83
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:06,752
- Well, they're out.
- You "drownded" me!

84
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:11,950
<i>Oh, don't worry.</i>
<i>I'll clean it up for you, Paulie.</i>

85
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,636
Da-da!

86
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:19,390
- Rocky!
- Yeah, you noticed.

87
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,875
What are you doing with that cake?

88
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:26,278
The party ain't over yet, you know.
We still gotta celebrate some more.

89
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:29,472
- It's a special night.
- Yeah, it's Wednesday.

90
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:32,160
It's Wednesday, but in case you forgot...

91
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:36,319
...it's almost been nine years since
you've been married to me, so...

92
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:38,396
...here's your prize.

93
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:43,230
- But our anniversary's a week away.
- That's true, but, uh... why wait?

94
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:46,750
- Has it been that rough?
- <i>(laughs)</i> No, no.

95
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:50,430
I tell you, it's been excellent.
Open your prize. Go on.

96
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:53,279
- Go on, open your prize.
- OK.

97
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,230
- Do you like it?
- It's beautiful.

98
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,555
All right!

99
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:03,877
I was so nervous. I didn't know.
I... I hope you like it.

100
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:08,597
The guy I bought it from says even if
it looks like a snake, don't worry...

101
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,995
...cos it won't bite you.

102
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,758
Oh! It's beautiful.

103
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:17,270
You know what's amazing?

104
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:21,552
That after all these years,
everything still seems kinda new.

105
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:25,996
You remember a long time ago
I told you that, uh...

106
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:30,352
...I said that you ain't never
gettin' rid of me. Remember that?

107
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,589
Well, you're not.

108
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:37,075
You're never gettin' rid of me.

109
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,476
Happy "almost anniversary".

110
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:55,474
<i>(barrage of questions)</i>

111
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:58,513
- A few questions, please.
- How long are you here for?

112
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:01,154
- We talk later.
- When are you gonna fight, Drago?

113
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:02,793
We talk later.

114
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:07,152
<i>(man)</i> Is it definite that the Soviet Union
will enter professional boxing?

115
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:10,716
No more talk now.
We will talk at press conference.

116
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:17,231
<i>(advert on TV)</i> # <i>Oh, golden dishes</i>
<i>from Church's and catfish at Church's</i>

117
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:20,716
# <i>Have some catfish from</i>
<i>Church's Fried Chicken</i>

118
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:23,195
# <i>Catfish from Church's!</i>

119
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:26,514
<i>Today may be a landmark</i>
<i>in sports history.</i>

120
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:30,679
<i>After unravelling years of red tape,</i>
<i>Russia will throw its hat into the ring -</i>

121
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:34,873
<i>the prize ring. The introductions were</i>
<i>made by his wife, Ludmilla Vobet Drago -</i>

122
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,831
<i>gold medallist in swimming.</i>

123
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:40,839
<i>Today the Soviet Union has officially</i>
<i>entered professional boxing.</i>

124
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:45,033
<i>My husband and great undefeated</i>
<i>heavyweight world amateur champion...</i>

125
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:48,994
<i>... Captain lvan Drago, has come here</i>
<i>with his trainers to America...</i>

126
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:53,352
<i>... to compete as an international</i>
<i>sportsman and ambassador of goodwill.</i>

127
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,789
<i>(man#1) Has he boxed</i>
<i>against a professional?</i>

128
00:08:55,920 --> 00:09:00,516
<i>From having been trained in Russia</i>
<i>by great boxing coach Manuel Vega...</i>

129
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:04,599
<i>... and now by Sergei Rimsky,</i>
<i>we hope he's qualified to do so.</i>

130
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,790
<i>- (man#1) Hope?</i>
<i>- Well, I know he is...</i>

131
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:09,878
<i>... but I don't want to sound too confident.</i>

132
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:14,790
<i>We would like an exhibition bout with</i>
<i>your famous champion, Rocky Balboa.</i>

133
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:18,151
<i>(man#2) You think he can fight</i>
<i>someone as seasoned as Balboa?</i>

134
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:22,319
<i>There is no one who can match his</i>
<i>strength, endurance or aggressiveness.</i>

135
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,590
<i>(man#3) You make him</i>
<i>sound indestructible.</i>

136
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,438
<i>Yes, he is.</i>

137
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:30,519
<i>(anchorman) Can this mammoth Russian,</i>
<i>nicknamed the Siberian Express...</i>

138
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:33,598
<i>... wreak havoc among</i>
<i>the professional heavyweight ranks?</i>

139
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:36,757
<i>Whoever he fights first,</i>
<i>it'll be one hot ticket.</i>

140
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:40,509
<i>We'll be right back with a check on</i>
<i>today's pro football sports scoreboard.</i>

141
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,754
<i>- (loud pop music)</i>
- Dad, when can I learn to fight?

142
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,951
- I can't hear you. What?
- I wanna learn to fight.

143
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:50,840
Yo. Could you turn your robot down?

144
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:54,712
You see, I fight so you don't have to fight.

145
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:59,277
I want you to use your head for somethin'
instead of a punchin' bag, like I do.

146
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:02,517
Your head doesn't look
like a punching bag.

147
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:05,393
No? That's nice. Thanks a lot.

148
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:07,670
It looks like a catcher's mitt!

149
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:10,598
Oh! A wise guy, huh?

150
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:13,190
Mr Balboa! Mr Creed's on the phone.

151
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,717
- Yeah? I'll be right there.
<i>- You can get it right here.</i>

152
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:20,799
- I hope it's not another rematch.
- Oh, don't worry about it.

153
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:23,673
Hello? Yeah, Apollo... Turn that down.

154
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:28,510
Apollo, how ya doin'? Yeah?
You're comin' out? That's great.

155
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:31,598
What am <i>I</i> doin'? I'm just gettin' dizzy.

156
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:39,478
My husband and I thank you for
coming to our training quarter today.

157
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:43,673
As you can see, it is highly advanced, and
we wish to show the American press...

158
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:47,110
...a small portion of the advances
our country has made...

159
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,390
...in the technology
of human performance.

160
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:52,751
<i>(man#1)</i> Coach Rimsky, what does
this do to enhance performance?

161
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,836
- Well...
- If I may answer.

162
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,517
It makes a man a better man...

163
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:03,031
...a great athlete a superathlete,
by harnessing all his strength.

164
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:06,118
Though most of the world is
ignorant in body chemistry...

165
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:10,791
...we wish to... educate your country.
- There have been rumours of doping...

166
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:14,833
...and widespread distribution of
anabolic steroids in the Soviet Union.

167
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:19,636
- Has Drago partaken in any experiments?
- No! Lvan is naturally trained.

168
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:22,718
Then how do you explain his,
uh... freakish strength?

169
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:26,037
Like your Popeye,
he ate his spinach every day.

170
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:32,112
- Shall we have a demonstration?
- <i>(man#1)</i> Please do.

171
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:37,958
A normal heavyweight averages
700 pounds of pressure per square inch.

172
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:53,116
As you can see,
Drago averages 1850 pounds.

173
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:56,910
- So the result's quite obvious.
- And what results are those?

174
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:59,838
Whatever he hits, he destroys.

175
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:05,670
I've seen Drago fight when he was an
amateur. He's big and strong, but clumsy.

176
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,155
I know I can beat him.

177
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:12,637
- Why do you wanna fight again?
- Let's just say it's somethin' <i>I</i> believe in.

178
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:16,833
- Uh, you can do your homework.
- OK. Later, Dad. Later, Uncle Paulie.

179
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,916
- Later, Apollo.
- Later, big man.

180
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:22,157
See you later, kiddo.
Don't you think people are expectin'...

181
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:27,513
...to see Rocky whack this bum out first?
- Yeah. And he will, when it's for real.

182
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:30,950
- This is an exhibition bout. Kids' stuff.
- What's the purpose?

183
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:35,119
What at this point in your life
is worth getting hurt for?

184
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:38,676
# <i>Double or nothin',</i>
<i>you've gotta have a partner...</i>

185
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:41,360
- What the hell is that?
- That's my girl.

186
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:45,431
# <i>Takin' and givin',</i>
<i>it's time we started livin'...</i>

187
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,274
- Thanks, honey.
<i>- (female voice) You're welcome.</i>

188
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:54,029
- That's a nice song.
<i>- It's my favourite. You're the greatest.</i>

189
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:56,675
<i>See you, sport.</i>

190
00:12:56,800 --> 00:13:00,031
- See you.
- Paulie, who taught it to talk like that?

191
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,876
- She loves me.
- Oh.

192
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:07,117
# <i>You stepped out of the night...</i>

193
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:13,514
Like I was sayin', I don't want this chump
to come over here with all that hype...

194
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:16,518
...tryin' to make us look bad.
They try every other way.

195
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:21,111
With Rock's help, we can get great
media coverage. We make <i>them</i> look bad.

196
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:24,357
- I think it's wrong.
- No. It's never been more right.

197
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:27,517
You're a great fighter,
but you've been retired five years.

198
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,234
Isn't it time to start
thinking about something else?

199
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:33,272
How much can you take? Either of you?

200
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,556
I'll... get the coffee.

201
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,598
Look, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...

202
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:46,075
I just care about you both. I...

203
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:53,035
You ever try these comics?

204
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:57,073
- No, no.
- Keeps your fertility.

205
00:13:58,120 --> 00:13:59,599
Hey, Paulie.

206
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:04,032
<i>In the ring now... Rocky's holding that</i>
<i>right hand. He's fighting right-handed!</i>

207
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:06,390
<i>(Apollo)</i> Oh, now this was a great fight.

208
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,193
Great(!) I'm gettin' punchy just watchin' it!

209
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:12,756
<i>Mamma mia!</i> What you usin'
for a chin there, Stallion?

210
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:18,355
- I should've slipped that one.
- You definitely should've slipped that.

211
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:23,349
It's crazy how people just care about you
in that ring and when you're bleedin'...

212
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:26,119
...but once you step out,
you're ancient history.

213
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,117
It ain't ancient history.

214
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:31,789
I don't see anybody askin'
for autographs, do you?

215
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:35,959
Hey, Apollo...
Can I, uh, ask you somethin'?

216
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,159
What?

217
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:42,671
Well, this fight you're havin' against
the Russian. Do you think maybe...

218
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,756
...it ain't against him?

219
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:48,955
If it's not him, Stallion,
then who's it against?

220
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:53,995
Well, do you think maybe it's, like, uh,
you against you? What do you think?

221
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:57,396
You know, I think you really
<i>are</i> gettin' brain-damaged.

222
00:14:57,520 --> 00:15:01,308
Maybe, but, uh... really.
I'm speakin' the truth here, Apollo.

223
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:04,000
- Are you?
- Yeah.

224
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:09,753
- I don't think I wanna hear this, Stallion.
- Hey, Apollo, you were a great fighter...

225
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,633
...but, look, we gotta face the facts too.

226
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:15,399
You don't wanna believe it,
but maybe the show is over.

227
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:18,512
That's easy for you to say.
You're still on top.

228
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:21,234
What happens when
you're not on top? Then what?

229
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:24,955
Where do we go, Stallion?
Cos we sure as hell can't be born again.

230
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:29,915
I know we can't be born again, but, let's
face it, we... we gotta change sometime.

231
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:32,474
I don't wanna change! I like who I am!

232
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:35,353
I like who you are, too, but look at that.

233
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:38,153
That ain't us up there no more, Apollo.

234
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:41,033
We can't do that the way we did it before.

235
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:44,709
We're changin'. We're, like,
turnin' into regular people.

236
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:47,912
No, Stallion!
Maybe you <i>think</i> you're changin'.

237
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:53,068
But you can't change what you really are.
You can forget all this money and stuff.

238
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,156
Cos it don't change a thing.

239
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:59,114
You and me, we don't even have a choice.

240
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:04,553
We're born with a killer instinct that you
can't just turn off and on like some radio.

241
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:08,355
We <i>have</i> to be right in the middle of
the action, cos we're the warriors.

242
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:11,153
Without some challenge,
some damn war to fight...

243
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:14,636
...then the warrior may
as well be dead, Stallion.

244
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,636
So I'm askin' you...

245
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,796
...as a friend...

246
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:29,152
...stand by my side this one last time.

247
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,355
You're a great talker, Apollo.

248
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:39,952
All right, but... when this is over...?

249
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,070
You know me, Stallion.

250
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,555
I always think of somethin' else.

251
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:51,919
That's what I'm afraid of.
All right. You got a deal there.

252
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:54,634
I feel sorry for that guy, you know?

253
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:58,790
<i>(man#1)</i> What made you decide to
put on an exhibition fight with Drago?

254
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,593
<i>(Apollo)</i> Let's call it
a sense of responsibility.

255
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,676
<i>(man#2)</i> Responsibility, how?

256
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:07,156
I had to teach this young fella
to box - American style!

257
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:10,192
Isn't Drago a little inexperienced
to be in the same ring?

258
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:13,790
Well, you know,
some folks got to learn the hard way!

259
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:18,470
- <i>(man#3)</i> No quick knockout predictions?
- No. I'm not angry with him.

260
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:23,230
I just wanna show the whole world that
Russia doesn't have all the best athletes.

261
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:26,557
Rocky, how do you think
Apollo should fight Drago?

262
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:31,879
Well, personally, I think the first thing
you'd better get Apollo is a ladder.

263
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:37,237
Drago, how does it feel to spar
with the great former champion?

264
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:42,275
The man's tongue didn't
come through customs.

265
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:46,160
My husband is very happy
to have this opportunity.

266
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:48,953
- It's his dream.
- <i>(man#4)</i> Dream? How do you mean?

267
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:52,959
In our country, Apollo Creed is
well known and very respected.

268
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:57,471
- It could be a good victory.
- Whoa! Wait a minute, now. Hold it.

269
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:02,355
When? Now you don't really think
you're gonna whip me, do ya?

270
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:06,189
- Well, he didn't come here to lose.
- You hold on, little lady.

271
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:09,756
- Lose, and lose royally, he's gonna do.
- How can you be so sure?

272
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:14,954
I've been with the best. I beat the best.
I retired more men than Social Security!

273
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:18,755
Excuse, please. You are not
very realistic, are you, Mr Creed?

274
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:20,791
What are <i>you</i> talkin' about?

275
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:24,629
You can box, yes, but you are far too
old to think you can win over Drago.

276
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:27,957
- Is that a fact?
- Yes! And it could be a painful one!

277
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:31,516
Put that heavy bag with eyeballs
in the ring with me and <i>you'll</i> see pain!

278
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:34,552
- Why do you insult us?
- Now you just hold on here.

279
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:38,195
I'm not the bad guy. I came to talk
about a friendly exhibition bout...

280
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:42,154
...till Comrade Bigmouth started up!
- It is <i>you</i> who are the aggressor.

281
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,999
I wish to say to the press, in all fairness...

282
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:48,590
...Drago should not even fight this man,
because he is a has-been.

283
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:51,871
You get that big chump
in the ring right now...

284
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:59,637
- Stop this before you get hurt.
- I don't wanna hear! Let that chump go!

285
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:05,995
All right, all right. I've said what I feel.

286
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:08,714
- We'll finish this in the ring!
- Wherever you like.

287
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:13,470
You shut up, and all these puppets you
brought with you! You're history, chump!

288
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,750
- How did I do?
- A little loud for me.

289
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,950
- But good?
- Oh, yeah. Very good.

290
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:25,717
<i>(announcer) Welcome to</i>
<i>the City of Lights - Las Vegas -</i>

291
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:29,719
<i>and to one of the most unusual</i>
<i>events in years: East meets West.</i>

292
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:33,476
<i>Age versus youth in</i>
<i>a goodwill exhibition match...</i>

293
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:37,229
<i>... as the former champion Apollo Creed</i>
<i>takes on a mountain of muscle...</i>

294
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:40,318
<i>... from the Soviet Union: Lvan Drago.</i>

295
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,271
- Come on.
- Patience is a virtue.

296
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:47,076
<i>- (Apollo)</i> I'm ready to rock 'n' roll.
- <i>(Rocky)</i> You gotta get your equipment.

297
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,794
- Now you look like a mummy.
- I feel like a mummy.

298
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:53,117
- How does it feel? OK?
- Feels great. I feel like I could eat nails.

299
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:56,471
- I never tried them snails.
- What are you talkin' about?

300
00:19:56,600 --> 00:20:00,388
Snails. I never had 'em. I see 'em in
the garden, but I never want to eat 'em.

301
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:05,833
I didn't say anythin' about snails.
I said nails. N-N-Nails, Stallion!

302
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,679
You look pretty good, but, you know...

303
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:11,268
...just do me a favour
when you go up there.

304
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:15,871
- Try not to wear yourself out, OK?
- Yeah, wear myself out. Sure.

305
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:19,117
Well, it's just that you ain't
been in the ring for five years.

306
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:23,950
- I just want you to... maintain a little bit.
- I'm in the best shape of my life.

307
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:28,232
- I'm stronger, I'm quicker...
- Hey, I'm not sayin' you're not ready...

308
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:30,874
...but personally, if it were me...

309
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,231
...I wouldn't mind postponin'
a couple of weeks.

310
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:36,237
Postpone?

311
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:40,831
Come on, Apollo. We don't know anythin'
about this guy you're fightin', really.

312
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:46,273
Let's say I postpone. I pull out, somebody
else steps in and whips this chump.

313
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:50,154
- Then where does that leave me?
- This is just some kind of exhibition fight.

314
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:53,909
- This thing don't mean nothin'.
- No, man. That's where you're wrong.

315
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:57,191
This is <i>not</i> just an exhibition fight
that doesn't mean anything.

316
00:20:57,320 --> 00:21:01,871
This is us against them.
What are you talkin' about? Come on!

317
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,956
Stallion...

318
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:09,757
Maybe you don't know what I'm talkin'
about now, but you will when it's over.

319
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:14,837
Believe me, you will when it's over.

320
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,635
<i>(speaks in Russian)</i>

321
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,031
Lvan!

322
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:56,357
Good luck. I hope after we can be friends.

323
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:59,593
- I hope so.
- Of course. They're sportsmen...

324
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:01,551
...not soldiers.

325
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,396
Enjoy the fight.

