372
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:19,158
Good evening.
Along with Warner Wolf, I am Stu Nahan.

373
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:22,352
We welcome you to an unusual
event: For the first time ever...

374
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,948
...West against East in professional sports.

375
00:25:25,080 --> 00:25:27,389
Thanks for gettin' me here. I owe you one.

376
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:30,398
- Oh, no, no. We're even.
- God, I feel born again.

377
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:33,717
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome!

378
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:38,072
I would like to announce the presence
of a true fighting champion...

379
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,350
...that defines the word "courage".

380
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:43,916
The Italian Stallion: Rocky Balboa!

381
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:49,034
- Excuse me, would you?
- Certainly.

382
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:53,596
Rocky!

383
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:57,437
<i>(bell rings)</i>

384
00:25:57,560 --> 00:26:01,314
Tonight's special event
features two great athletes.

385
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:04,989
In the blue corner,
weighing 221 pounds...

386
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:08,351
...a former heavyweight
champion of the world...

387
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,914
...the Dancing Destroyer...

388
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,110
...the King of Sting...

389
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:15,708
...the Count of Monte Fisto...

390
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:18,991
- Think you got enough names?
- Be patient. Almost done.

391
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:24,797
The Master of Disaster,
the one and only Apollo Creed!

392
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:33,150
<i>(Stu)</i> The crowd anticipating a great
fight now as Apollo plays to the crowd.

393
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:41,160
In the red corner,
weighing an even 261 pounds...

394
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:45,432
...gold medallist and undefeated
world amateur champion...

395
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:48,074
...from the Soviet Union...

396
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:50,156
...the Siberian Bull...

397
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:53,390
...lvan Drago!

398
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:55,317
<i>(booing)</i>

399
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:01,152
I want you! I want <i>you!</i> I want <i>you!</i>

400
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:05,876
<i>(Stu)</i> The two fighters come to the centre
for instructions from referee Lou Filippo.

401
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:10,357
You know the rules. Watch the low blows,
kidney punches and rabbit punches.

402
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:14,871
In case of a knockdown, go to the corner
and stay there until I tell you to come out.

403
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:19,391
- Shake hands. Let's have a good fight.
- It's time to go to school, son.

404
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:24,548
Get your hands up! Do you need an
interpreter? It's time to go to school!

405
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:27,035
You will lose.

406
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:30,711
All right!

407
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:34,196
<i>(Stu)</i> The bad blood between these two
can be felt all over this arena.

408
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:37,198
I can't get over the size of this Russian!

409
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,557
- Apollo! Apollo!
- Get ready, cos it's showtime! Showtime!

410
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:46,800
- It's showtime!
- Excuse me. Didn't you forget somethin'?

411
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,036
Apollo seems to be in great spirits.

412
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:53,073
He's really putting on a show
for this capacity crowd.

413
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,553
Be back in a minute, all right?

414
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:58,711
<i>(Stu)</i> Round one.

415
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,432
Creed's dancing around.

416
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:05,075
Creed back-pedalling now.
He's been away five years.

417
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:19,713
Neither fighter ready to throw a punch.
A left jab there... and once again.

418
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,800
- A slip by Creed.
- <i>(Warner)</i> This is bizarre.

419
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:30,311
Creed is over the hill, and, uh...
the Russian hasn't fought anybody.

420
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,838
- Keep movin'. Stick him!
- <i>(Stu)</i> Drago's moving in again.

421
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:46,272
A left hand by Creed. Another left hand
by Creed, and Drago moves away.

422
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:57,830
Another left hand by Creed. Drago
waiting, waiting, cocking that right hand.

423
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,638
<i>(shouts in Russian)</i>

424
00:29:00,320 --> 00:29:03,153
<i>(Warner)</i> Ooh! A punishing right
by the Russian.

425
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:06,033
Get outta there! Get outta there!

426
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:10,199
<i>(Stu)</i> A left. He's taking some punishment
now. Drago moves him against the ropes.

427
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,469
Tie him up now!

428
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:15,229
<i>(Stu)</i> The Russian ties him up
and throws Creed across the ring!

429
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,351
Move!

430
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:20,637
<i>(Stu)</i> It is Drago with the upper hand now.

431
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,591
Get outta that corner!

432
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:25,188
<i>(Stu)</i> Another right! Another right!

