What a horrendous flight.

655
00:47:16,760 --> 00:47:19,877
This is Russia?
It don't look so tough, Rock.

656
00:47:44,680 --> 00:47:46,750
Mr Balboa.

657
00:47:46,880 --> 00:47:48,233
<i>(speaks Russian)</i>

658
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:51,113
We take you to quarters now.

659
00:47:51,240 --> 00:47:55,358
Hey, when does the sun come up?
This is detrimental to my sinuses.

660
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:59,151
Weather changes, hour to hour.
Get used to it.

661
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:00,474
<i>(speaks Russian)</i>

662
00:48:00,600 --> 00:48:04,229
Get in car now. We have very long trip.

663
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:06,715
He sounds like Dracula's cousin.

664
00:48:09,520 --> 00:48:13,035
# <i>In the warrior's code</i>
<i>there's no surrender</i>

665
00:48:14,040 --> 00:48:19,114
# <i>Though his body says "Stop",</i>
<i>his spirit cries "Never!"</i>

666
00:48:19,240 --> 00:48:22,596
# <i>Deep in our soul a quiet ember</i>

667
00:48:23,160 --> 00:48:25,196
# <i>Knows it's you against you</i>

668
00:48:25,680 --> 00:48:29,389
# <i>It's the paradox that drives us on</i>

669
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:32,750
# <i>It's a battle of wills</i>

670
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:37,510
# <i>In the heat of attack,</i>
<i>it's the passion that kills</i>

671
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:41,952
# <i>That victory is yours alone</i>

672
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:45,189
# <i>In the burning heart</i>

673
00:48:45,320 --> 00:48:47,436
# <i>Just about to burst</i>

674
00:48:47,560 --> 00:48:52,076
# <i>There's a quest for answers,</i>
<i>an unquenchable thirst</i>

675
00:48:52,200 --> 00:48:56,751
# <i>In the darkest night, rising like a spire</i>

676
00:48:56,880 --> 00:49:01,556
# <i>In the burning heart,</i>
<i>the unmistakable fire</i>

677
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:06,789
Like you requested, yes?

678
00:49:06,920 --> 00:49:09,593
- You requested this dumb location?
- Yeah.

679
00:49:10,160 --> 00:49:13,357
Why? You plannin' to grow
reindeer or somethin'?

680
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:20,438
- I just wanted to get away from things.
- The equipment you requested is in barn.

681
00:49:23,360 --> 00:49:26,193
- Who are they?
- They?

682
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:28,993
They are assigned to you.

683
00:49:29,120 --> 00:49:31,680
Official chaperons, yes?

684
00:49:31,800 --> 00:49:33,995
Where you go, they go.

685
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:37,150
Oh, I have a bad dream here.

686
00:49:38,040 --> 00:49:42,272
- Paul, it's OK.
- OK? This is below human standards.

687
00:49:42,400 --> 00:49:46,632
There's no antennas.
You gotta complain. We'll crack out here!

688
00:49:46,760 --> 00:49:49,957
You have everything
I have been instructed to provide.

689
00:49:50,080 --> 00:49:54,153
We are finished, yes? <i>Da svidaniya.</i>

690
00:50:03,720 --> 00:50:05,676
<i>(Paulie)</i> No sparrin'?

691
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:11,352
I don't think I need it any more, Paulie.

692
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:13,789
No sparrin', no TV, nothin'?

693
00:50:14,200 --> 00:50:17,192
How the heck is he supposed
to train around here?

694
00:50:17,760 --> 00:50:20,433
No TV. What about the Rose Bowl game?

695
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:24,719
No room service, I bet.
I hope they got my comics here.

696
00:50:24,840 --> 00:50:27,229
What a depressing vacation.

697
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:30,039
Aagh!

698
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:33,156
Aagh!

699
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:36,316
Goddamn!

700
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:44,396
<i>(tape) All right, you Chipmunks.</i>
<i>Ready to sing your song?</i>

701
00:50:44,520 --> 00:50:48,308
# <i>Christmas, Christmastime is here</i>

702
00:50:48,840 --> 00:50:53,152
# <i>Time for toys and time for cheer</i>

703
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:57,478
# <i>We've been good, but we can't last...</i>

704
00:50:57,600 --> 00:51:00,160
Checkmate, friend.

705
00:51:11,040 --> 00:51:13,076
<i>(knock at door)</i>

706
00:51:13,200 --> 00:51:16,078
- Yeah?
- Hey, champ. Can I come up?

707
00:51:16,200 --> 00:51:18,156
Yeah, sure.

708
00:51:20,520 --> 00:51:22,590
- How you doin'?
- Pretty good.

709
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:26,793
- Some kinda weather we're havin', huh?
- Yeah, it's pretty rough.

710
00:51:26,920 --> 00:51:29,480
But for what you gotta do, it's good.

711
00:51:31,040 --> 00:51:33,793
- Toughen you up.
- I guess so.

712
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:38,311
I know you're gonna have to do almost
everything alone, but I'll be with you.

713
00:51:38,440 --> 00:51:40,396
Yeah, I know.

714
00:51:40,520 --> 00:51:43,398
Apollo was like my son.

715
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:45,954
I raised him.

716
00:51:46,080 --> 00:51:48,548
And when he died... a part of me died.

717
00:51:50,640 --> 00:51:53,279
But now... <i>you're</i> the one.

718
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:57,552
You're the one that's gonna keep
his spirit alive. You're the one...

719
00:51:57,680 --> 00:52:01,639
...that's gonna make sure
that he didn't die for nothing.

720
00:52:01,760 --> 00:52:04,638
Now you're gonna have
to go through hell...

721
00:52:04,760 --> 00:52:07,797
...worse than any nightmare
that you ever dreamed.

722
00:52:08,080 --> 00:52:12,835
But in the end...
I know you'll be the one standin'.

723
00:52:14,560 --> 00:52:16,516
I'll try.

724
00:52:19,440 --> 00:52:21,396
I'll try.

725
00:52:25,320 --> 00:52:27,276
You know what you gotta do.

726
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:31,635
Do it.

727
00:52:32,040 --> 00:52:33,996
Do it!

728
00:52:39,120 --> 00:52:41,076
Thanks, Duke.

729
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:46,675
I couldn't stay away any more.

730
00:56:50,040 --> 00:56:52,395
I missed you.

731
00:56:54,520 --> 00:56:57,080
I missed <i>you.</i>

732
00:56:57,760 --> 00:57:00,513
I'm with you, no matter what.

733
00:57:00,800 --> 00:57:02,756
No matter what?

734
00:57:05,280 --> 00:57:07,430
No matter what.

735
00:57:29,800 --> 00:57:31,916
<i>(</i># <i>"Heart's on Fire" by John Cafferty)</i>

736
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:55,318
# <i>Silent darkness creeps into your soul</i>

737
00:57:57,760 --> 00:58:02,117
# <i>And removes the light of self-control</i>

738
00:58:04,480 --> 00:58:08,951
# <i>The cage that holds</i>
<i>you captive has no doors</i>

739
00:58:11,520 --> 00:58:14,512
# <i>Burnin' with determination</i>

740
00:58:14,640 --> 00:58:17,200
# <i>To even out the score</i>

741
00:58:17,920 --> 00:58:21,435
# <i>Heart's on fire</i>

742
00:58:21,560 --> 00:58:24,950
# <i>Strong desire</i>

743
00:58:25,080 --> 00:58:29,039
# <i>Rages deep within</i>

744
00:58:31,560 --> 00:58:34,677
# <i>Heart's on fire</i>

745
00:58:34,800 --> 00:58:39,715
# <i>Fever's risin' high</i>

746
00:58:43,480 --> 00:58:45,835
# <i>The moment of truth is here</i>

747
00:58:47,360 --> 00:58:49,316
# <i>Oh!</i>

748
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:55,879
No pain. No pain.

749
00:59:25,720 --> 00:59:28,757
# <i>Heart's on fire</i>

750
00:59:28,880 --> 00:59:32,589
# <i>Strong desire</i>

751
00:59:32,720 --> 00:59:36,759
# <i>Rages deep within</i>

752
00:59:39,440 --> 00:59:41,954
# <i>Fever's risin'</i>

753
00:59:42,440 --> 00:59:45,432
# <i>Energisin'</i>

754
00:59:45,880 --> 00:59:49,714
# <i>Fight until the end</i>

755
00:59:52,800 --> 00:59:55,792
# <i>Heart's on fire</i>

756
00:59:55,920 --> 00:59:59,435
# <i>Strong desire</i>

757
00:59:59,560 --> 01:00:03,792
# <i>Rages deep within</i>

758
01:01:17,080 --> 01:01:20,595
Drago!

759
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:25,677
Drago!

760
01:01:28,400 --> 01:01:32,837
Drago!

761
01:01:34,680 --> 01:01:37,478
Hello, and merry Christmas
from a very unusual place.

762
01:01:37,600 --> 01:01:41,639
We're in Moscow. I'm Barry Tompkins,
along with Al Bandiero...

763
01:01:41,760 --> 01:01:45,548
...and this promises to be the most
watched event in boxing history.

764
01:01:45,680 --> 01:01:50,629
The Iron Horse from America, Rocky
Balboa, comes here to the Soviet Union...

765
01:01:52,040 --> 01:01:56,750
Ivan Drago: Since that tragedy in Las
Vegas and the death of Apollo Creed...

766
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:59,872
...he's been re-nicknamed
"Death from Above".

767
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:13,120
<i>(chanting)</i> Drago! Drago!

768
01:02:30,480 --> 01:02:34,553
The general secretary of the Soviet
and other members of the Politburo...

769
01:02:34,680 --> 01:02:39,435
...have now made their way to their seats
high above the ring here in Moscow.

770
01:02:44,520 --> 01:02:49,036
I know you're kinda busy, but I wanna
tell you some things I never told you.

771
01:02:49,160 --> 01:02:54,029
I know sometimes I act stupid and I say
stupid things, but you kept me around...

772
01:02:54,160 --> 01:02:58,119
...when other people would've said
"Drop that bum." You give me respect.

773
01:02:58,240 --> 01:03:01,949
It's hard for me to say these kinda
things because that ain't my way...

774
01:03:02,080 --> 01:03:07,234
...but if I could unzip myself and step out
and be someone else, I'd wanna be you.

775
01:03:07,360 --> 01:03:09,316
You're all heart, Rock.

776
01:03:11,760 --> 01:03:13,876
Thanks, Paulie.

777
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:16,070
Now blast this guy's teeth out!

778
01:03:17,240 --> 01:03:19,708
I'll try.

779
01:03:26,400 --> 01:03:28,356
<i>(booing)</i>

780
01:03:34,000 --> 01:03:38,437
One of the fighters is starting to make his
way through this crowd toward the ring.

781
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:42,712
- Listen to this crowd!
- <i>(Al)</i> This borders on pure hatred.

782
01:03:42,840 --> 01:03:47,516
<i>(Barry)</i> Rocky's face: Absolutely like
stone, a picture of concentration...

783
01:03:47,640 --> 01:03:50,677
...and the booing crowd here does
not seem to bother him one bit.

784
01:03:50,800 --> 01:03:53,360
The champ has a look that
could burn through lead.

785
01:03:53,480 --> 01:03:57,109
It seems the booing crowd has
absolutely no effect on the man.

786
01:03:57,240 --> 01:03:59,231
His concentration is like stone.

787
01:03:59,360 --> 01:04:01,635
- That's my dad.
- We know.

788
01:04:01,760 --> 01:04:04,035
What do you think we are - nerds?

789
01:04:04,160 --> 01:04:06,993
<i>(Al)</i> Listen to this crowd. It sounds insane.

790
01:04:07,840 --> 01:04:09,796
<i>(booing and jeering)</i>

791
01:04:14,280 --> 01:04:18,034
<i>(Barry)</i> And now the entrance
of the Russian national champion.

792
01:04:18,160 --> 01:04:22,472
Ivan Drago, a man with
an entire country in his corner.

793
01:05:12,960 --> 01:05:15,838
Look at the expression
on the face of lvan Drago.

794
01:05:15,960 --> 01:05:18,997
He seems impervious
to this madness of the crowd.

795
01:05:19,120 --> 01:05:21,873
He's like a volcano just waiting to erupt.

796
01:05:22,000 --> 01:05:26,516
<i>(English commentator)</i> The Russian is
cool as he acknowledges his premier.

797
01:05:28,080 --> 01:05:32,073
I would like to point out again,
this is a non-sanctioned fight.

798
01:05:32,200 --> 01:05:37,479
This is not for the title. The American
Boxing Commission has not sanctioned it.

799
01:05:53,760 --> 01:05:55,830
<i>(</i># <i>Soviet national anthem)</i>

800
01:07:08,680 --> 01:07:10,796
Ladies and gentlemen...

801
01:07:10,920 --> 01:07:12,876
<i>(speaks Russian)</i>

802
01:07:18,440 --> 01:07:20,078
Rocky Balboa!

803
01:07:20,200 --> 01:07:22,350
<i>(booing and jeering)</i>

804
01:07:24,440 --> 01:07:29,389
<i>(Englishman)</i> It's unbelievable.
I have never seen such a hostile crowd.

805
01:07:29,520 --> 01:07:32,478
<i>(announcer speaks Russian)</i>

806
01:07:35,080 --> 01:07:37,640
<i>(speaks Russian)</i>

807
01:07:37,760 --> 01:07:39,557
Lvan Drago!

808
01:07:49,600 --> 01:07:54,720
<i>(Englishman)</i> Roaring for their champion!
The two men are walking to the centre.

809
01:07:54,840 --> 01:07:57,752
It's an unbelievable sight to see.

810
01:07:57,880 --> 01:07:59,836
They're toe to toe.

811
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:04,750
The Russian towers above the American.
It's a true case of David and Goliath here.

812
01:08:04,880 --> 01:08:08,589
It's unbelievable, the...
the condition of both men.

813
01:08:09,760 --> 01:08:11,990
I must break you.

814
01:08:18,080 --> 01:08:21,436
Remember what I said
about wanting to be you?

815
01:08:21,560 --> 01:08:23,516
Forget it.

816
01:08:24,440 --> 01:08:26,396
Thanks, Paul.

817
01:08:34,240 --> 01:08:37,755
Take it straight to him,
and be a rock for me, you understand?

818
01:08:37,880 --> 01:08:41,555
Be a rock for me! Be strong!
All right? Take it to him! No pain.

819
01:08:41,680 --> 01:08:44,990
- No pain. No pain.
- No pain. No pain. All right, Rock. Do it!

820
01:08:47,600 --> 01:08:50,831
<i>(Barry)</i> There's the bell.
Rocky comes to the centre of the ring...

821
01:08:50,960 --> 01:08:54,748
...like the Russian, way back
into Balboa's corner now.

822
01:08:59,080 --> 01:09:02,277
<i>- (Paulie)</i> Get outta there!
<i>- (Duke)</i> Let's go, Rocky!

823
01:09:05,520 --> 01:09:10,355
<i>(Barry)</i> Balboa gets out of the corner, and
it is Drago backing Rocky up with a jab.

824
01:09:10,480 --> 01:09:15,759
And Balboa is not staying on balance
because of the long jab of the Russian.

825
01:09:15,880 --> 01:09:18,075
Brace yourself! Brace yourself!

826
01:09:22,960 --> 01:09:25,315
<i>(Duke)</i> Hands up!

827
01:09:26,200 --> 01:09:27,872
- Charge him!
- Now!

828
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:30,798
<i>(Englishman)</i> He can't seem
to touch the Russian.

829
01:09:30,920 --> 01:09:35,550
<i>(Barry)</i> Rocky pounding away, and he's
just hit him with everything he's got.

830
01:09:35,680 --> 01:09:38,194
<i>(Al)</i> And Drago just smiled at him.

831
01:09:39,880 --> 01:09:43,077
- <i>(Duke)</i> Keep choppin' away!
- Chop him down! Chop him down!

832
01:09:48,680 --> 01:09:51,240
<i>(Barry)</i> Rocky Balboa
is in serious trouble!

833
01:09:51,360 --> 01:09:54,352
They might have to stop this one
before somebody gets killed.

834
01:09:54,480 --> 01:09:57,517
<i>(Duke)</i> Reach and grab him!
Reach and grab him!

835
01:09:59,800 --> 01:10:03,349
<i>(Barry)</i> Rocky woke the sleeping giant,
and now he's paying the price!

836
01:10:03,480 --> 01:10:07,598
A right hand from Drago sends Rocky
Balboa 15 feet across the ring...

837
01:10:07,720 --> 01:10:10,075
...and the champ is down!

838
01:10:15,280 --> 01:10:17,635
Come on! Get up!

839
01:10:19,920 --> 01:10:21,956
<i>(Duke)</i> Hands up! Hands up!

840
01:10:28,240 --> 01:10:33,519
<i>(Barry)</i> Drago continuing to punish Rocky.
He will not let him out of that corner...

841
01:10:33,640 --> 01:10:38,031
...and Rocky Balboa is just trying to
get through this first round.

842
01:10:38,920 --> 01:10:40,876
<i>(bell)</i>

843
01:10:42,360 --> 01:10:46,831
<i>(Al)</i> The Russian just threw Rocky Balboa
into his own corner like a rag doll.

844
01:10:46,960 --> 01:10:49,394
What a tough three minutes
for Rocky Balboa.

845
01:10:49,520 --> 01:10:52,432
He's not only fighting
an invincible opponent...

846
01:10:52,560 --> 01:10:54,915
...he's also fighting a hostile crowd...

847
01:10:55,040 --> 01:10:59,238
...and the Russian premier and
most of the Politburo looking on.

848
01:10:59,360 --> 01:11:02,670
- What's happenin' out there?
- He's winnin'.

849
01:11:03,840 --> 01:11:06,718
- I see three of him out there.
- Hit the one in the middle.

850
01:11:06,840 --> 01:11:09,798
- Right! Hit the one in the middle!
- Yeah.

851
01:11:09,920 --> 01:11:12,229
You're not doing as you're told.

852
01:11:12,680 --> 01:11:15,353
The American is small and weak...

853
01:11:15,680 --> 01:11:16,999
Weak.

854
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:22,035
Take his heart. If you hurt him, you'll take
his heart. No pain! Keep workin'!

855
01:11:22,160 --> 01:11:24,310
<i>(bell)</i>

856
01:11:24,440 --> 01:11:27,079
<i>(Barry)</i> Round two.
It's been a one-sided fight so far.

857
01:11:27,200 --> 01:11:30,909
<i>(Al)</i> lt'll take more than luck
for Rocky to survive this round.

858
01:11:31,160 --> 01:11:33,276
Slip him a hook, Rock! Slip him a hook!

859
01:11:33,400 --> 01:11:38,269
<i>(Barry)</i> Balboa trying to stay in the middle
of the ring against the big Russian.

860
01:11:40,720 --> 01:11:43,314
Do what you gotta do! Stay with him!

861
01:11:48,600 --> 01:11:51,990
<i>(Barry)</i> For all intent,
Balboa should be all finished...

862
01:11:52,120 --> 01:11:54,714
...but he's fighting back ferociously.

863
01:11:58,720 --> 01:12:00,676
Rocky!

864
01:12:01,680 --> 01:12:06,674
<i>(Barry)</i> Balboa goes down again from
a right hand! Bounces right back up.

865
01:12:07,600 --> 01:12:09,750
He's gettin' killed out there!

866
01:12:12,920 --> 01:12:16,469
<i>(Barry)</i> Rocky Balboa has taken
lvan Drago's best punches so far.

867
01:12:16,600 --> 01:12:21,196
He's cut and he's bleeding,
but he's on his feet and he's on the run!

868
01:12:26,920 --> 01:12:29,593
- He's cut! He's cut!
- <i>(Al)</i> The Russian's cut!

869
01:12:29,720 --> 01:12:34,669
<i>(Barry)</i> And it's a bad cut! And now it's
Rocky Balboa coming after lvan Drago!

870
01:12:44,200 --> 01:12:45,838
Incredible! Get him!

871
01:12:48,120 --> 01:12:50,429
<i>(bell)</i>

872
01:12:50,560 --> 01:12:53,836
<i>(Barry)</i> Drago wants to go on!
He grabs Balboa by the throat!

873
01:12:53,960 --> 01:12:58,078
Balboa picking up the Russian and throws
him to the ground like a wrestler.

874
01:12:58,200 --> 01:13:02,034
It's a gutter war!
No holds barred in Moscow!

875
01:13:02,160 --> 01:13:05,516
Rocky may be on the receiving end
so far, but he's here to fight.

876
01:13:05,640 --> 01:13:08,552
This is shaping up to be
a personal war, and right now...

877
01:13:08,680 --> 01:13:11,319
...it's anybody's boxing match.

878
01:13:12,680 --> 01:13:16,468
You're doin' good, Rocko.
I couldn't do better myself.

879
01:13:16,800 --> 01:13:17,949
How can you do this?

